	<body text="readme.md">
		<outline text="# mail">
			<outline text="One place to send mail from all my Node apps. "></outline>
			<outline text="* I was scattering this code everywhere. Now I have a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.npmjs.com/package/davemail&quot;&gt;package&lt;/a&gt;. "></outline>
			<outline text="* It builds on &lt;a href=&quot;https://aws.amazon.com/ses/&quot;&gt;Amazon's SES&lt;/a&gt;. "></outline>
			<outline text="* One routine for all your mail-sending needs: mail.send."></outline>
			<outline text="* Limits mail sending to 10 messages per second, to comply with AWS&quot;s rate limits. It keeps a queue so you can call it as fast as you like. "></outline>
			<outline text="* I use this code to send the &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/email/&quot;&gt;nightly emails&lt;/a&gt; from Scripting News. "></outline>
			</outline>
		<outline text="### Example">
			<outline text="```javascript"></outline>
			<outline text="const mail = require (&quot;davemail&quot;);"></outline>
			<outline text="mail.send (recipient, subject, message, sender);"></outline>
			<outline text="```"></outline>
			</outline>
		</body>
	</opml>
